Remember, the &quot;light bulb&quot; GCNR uses special giant glass cylinders containing fearsomely radioactive GASES at 100,000 degrees or so, located in an open thrust chamber with giant open nozzles.<br>
<br>
Consider as a scenario an event which has already occured in an arianne launch.<br>
<br>
A software glich causes the computers to throw the rocket out of control - MUCH MUCH faster than a human could respond to. The rocket tumbles out of control - being instanly torn apart by aerodynamic forces. The thrust chambers - minus any functioning control power, or working equipment hurtle any number of thousands of miles til they impact - where?<br>
<br>
As I posted earlier - responsible engineering design requires that you assume that none of the protective mechanisms would be available - which is a quite reasonable position.<br>
<br>
<br>
